deck: Xavier Fauche is a born storyteller, a versatile  writer who has worked, apart from comic books, in radio, TV and cinema. He has also written novels and essays and has been an active member of various organizations, including the Society of Dramatic Authors and Composers.
description:
His career starts in 1975, in the radio, where he directs various dramatic series. With Jean Leturgie he makes Cedric Lebihan and Percevan, as well as various issues of Lucky Luke and Rantanplan, demonstrating a fast adaptation and a complete comprehension of the language in comic books. He works in TV, in Fraggle Rock, Lucky Luke and Les Tiffous, and then goes back to the radio. He writes various books, including novels and essays, and also gives a try to screenplay writing, showing the versatility of his talent. He creates a Society specialized in comic books communication and administrates the Society of Dramatic Authors and Composers. He is a member of the swiss Board of Trade and of the local commission of town-planning, environment and culture at Saint-Cloud.

In 1996 he received the french Order of Arts and Letters, given to personalities who have "significantly contributed to the enrichment of french cultural inheritance".
name: Xavier Fauche

deck: DC/Aspen artist, who is known for his work on the New 52 Justice League and Batman Eternal. He worked on Justice League vs Suicide Squad's first issue.
description:
Career

After mentoring under fellow Canadian artist David Finch, Fabok got his big break when he was brought on to illustrated the final two issues of Finch's Batman: The Dark Knight which Finch fell behind on due to writing duties. Shortly after that, Fabok signed an exclusive contract with DC comics. With the launch of The New 52 Fabok drew various covers as well as the first Batman Annual as well as the Justice League International Annual, before taking over artist duties on the relaunched Detective Comics with issue #13, with new writer John Layman.

Fabok also recently worked on the first three issues of the weekly series Batman Eternal and will continue work on the series alongside a rotating group of artists.
name: Jason Fabok
